So I went to Potbelly on 4th street, ordered the chicken pot pie soup and it was amazing.  I signed up for the email notifications and received a free soup.  Told my coworkers and we went as a group where we were informed we couldn't use our coupons.  The coupon reads that we print it out and bring it in within 28 days.  The date on the email was 11/7/2018 and today is the 9th of November.  The manager was rude and kept saying Corporate wont allow for them to use the coupon unless its through the app.  Even after reading it was to be printed and brought in, he still wouldn't honor our coupons.  I wont be back.  And this time..the soup was NOT good.

This restaurant is located smack in the center of downtown Louisville's business/restaurant district.  Because I work in the area, I have lots of choices when it comes to lunch, but Potbelly, without a doubt, is my absolute favorite.  The food is always fresh and made just the way that I ask, and their prices won't break your budget.  Great soups, sandwiches, and salads, and their ranch dressing is the best I have ever had.   I am greeted with a smile the second I am noticed, and I have loved being their customer over the last few years.  Unfortunately, our office is relocating, and I will miss this place sorely.  The manager, Tom, and his crew are so incredibly sweet.  If you want good food and good service, this is your go-to place.

Accidents happen, however, when I called the store to place my complaint and spoke with the GENERAL MANAGER named DUSTIN, he "assured me" all of their turkey is precooked, and even after me stating that turkey is NEVER pink if it is in fact cooked, he just kept repeating himself and never offered any type of compensation for this inconvenience, nor did he ever try to apologize.
